What is Fynbos?

  • Fynbos is a Mediterranean type ecosystem, and the only biome found within the political boundaries of 1 country: South Africa.
  • At 90 000 square kilometers, it is the size of Portugal
  • although it is only 7.377% of South Africa
  • Rain falls mainly in winter, it is nutrient poor, and ecological processes depend on fire.
  • There are six species of birds found only in this Biome:


Cape Rockjumper


Victorin's Warbler


Cape Sugarbird


Orange-breasted Sunbird


Protea Seedeater


Cape Siskin
